  "prompt": "What is the average salary of IT professional having 10 years experience in India?",
  "response": "The average salary of an IT professional with 10 years of experience in India can vary significantly based on several factors:\n\n*   **Role:** Different IT roles command different salaries. For example, a software engineer typically earns differently than a data scientist or a project manager.\n*   **Skills and Technology:** In-demand skills and technologies like cloud computing (AWS, Azure, GCP), data science, AI/ML, DevOps, cybersecurity, and specific programming languages (Python, Java, etc.) often lead to higher salaries.\n*   **Company:** Large multinational corporations (MNCs) and product-based companies generally pay more than smaller service-based companies or startups.\n*   **Location:** Metropolitan cities like Bangalore, Mumbai, Hyderabad, and Delhi NCR tend to offer higher salaries due to the higher cost of living and concentration of IT companies.\n*   **Education and Certifications:** A higher degree (like a Master's) or relevant certifications can positively influence salary.\n\n**General Estimate:**\n\nConsidering these factors, a broad estimate for the average salary of an IT professional with 10 years of experience in India would fall within the range of **\u20b915,00,000 to \u20b935,00,000 per annum (INR 15 LPA to INR 35 LPA)**.\n\n**Detailed Break down based on roles**\n\nHere is breakdown for some specific roles to get a better estimate:\n\n*   **Software Engineer:** \u20b915,00,000 - \u20b925,00,000 per annum\n*   **Data Scientist:** \u20b920,00,000 - \u20b935,00,000 per annum\n*   **Project Manager:** \u20b918,00,000 - \u20b930,00,000 per annum\n*   **DevOps Engineer:** \u20b918,00,000 - \u20b932,00,000 per annum\n*   **Cloud Architect:** \u20b922,00,000 - \u20b940,00,000 per annum\n\n**How to Get a More Accurate Estimate:**\n\n*   **Use Online Salary Aggregators:** Websites like Glassdoor, AmbitionBox, Salary.com, and Payscale provide salary data based on job title, experience, location, and company.\n*   **Network with IT Professionals:** Connect with people in your field on LinkedIn or at industry events to get a sense of current salary trends.\n*   **Consult Recruiters:** IT recruiters have insights into salary ranges for different roles and skill sets.\n\n**Important Considerations:**\n\n*   The \"average\" is just a central tendency. Individual salaries can vary widely.\n*   Benefits and perks (health insurance, stock options, bonuses, etc.) are an important part of the total compensation package.\n*   Negotiation skills can significantly impact the final salary offer.\n\n**Disclaimer:** This information is for general guidance only and should not be considered definitive financial advice. Always do your own research to get the most up-to-date and relevant information.",
